<p>
Only some of the regular polygons can be built by <a href=3D"https://mathwo=
rld.wolfram.com/GeometricConstruction.html">geometric construction</a> usin=
g a <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Compass.html">compass</a> and =
<a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Straightedge.html">straightedge</a=
>.
 The numbers of sides for which regular polygons are <a href=3D"https://mat=
hworld.wolfram.com/ConstructiblePolygon.html">constructible</a>
 are those having central angles corresponding to so-called <a href=3D"http=
s://mathworld.wolfram.com/TrigonometryAngles.html">trigonometry
 angles</a>.
</p>
